kinetic.client

Interface CallbackResult<T>


  • public interface CallbackResult<T>
    Asynchronous callback result interface.

    When applications call a KineticClient asynchronous operation, the result is delivered to the registered callback handler. Kinetic client runtime library calls the CallbackHandler.onSuccess(CallbackResult) for each successful asynchronous operation.

    The Param Type matches the corresponding return type for its synchronous API variation. For example, a KineticClient.putForced(Entry) operation would have a CallbackResult of type Entry.

    See Also:
    CallbackHandler.onSuccess(CallbackResult), KineticClient
